The paper focuses on sentiment analysis for software engineering (SE) texts, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed model is based on convolutional neural networks (CNN) and long short-term memory (LSTM), which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as sentiment analysis (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of pre-trained word vectors, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and NLP (cs.CL). The paper evaluates the model's performance on gold standard datasets, which is a common practice in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.AI) research.
